org.matsim.core.network.algorithms

Class NetworkTeleatlasAddManeuverRestrictions

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.core.network.algorithms.NetworkTeleatlasAddManeuverRestrictions
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NetworkRunnable

    public final class NetworkTeleatlasAddManeuverRestrictions
extends Object
implements NetworkRunnable
    Adds maneuver restrictions to a MATSim network created by NetworkReaderTeleatlas. The input maneuver shape file and the maneuver path DBF file is based on Tele Atlas MultiNet Shapefile 4.3.2.1 Format Specifications document version Final v1.0, June 2007.
    Author:
    balmermi

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run(Network network)
        Reading and assigning (expanding nodes) maneuver restrictions to the network.

        It uses the following attributes from the Tele Atlas MultiNet maneuver Shape file:

        • MN_ID_NAME (Feature Identification)
        • MN_FEATTYP_NAME (Feature Type)
          • 9401: Bifurcation
          • 2104: Priority Maneuver
          • 2103: Prohibited Maneuver
          • 2102: Restricted Maneuver
          • 2101: Calculated/Derived Prohibited Maneuver
        • MN_JNCTID_NAME (Junction Identification of the Location of the Maneuver Sign)

        And it uses the following attributes from the Tele Atlas MultiNet maneuver path DBF file:

        • MP_ID_NAME (Feature Identification)
        • MP_SEQNR_NAME (Transportation Element Sequential Number within the Maneuver)
        • MP_TRPELID_NAME (Transportation Element Identification)

        Conversion rules:

        • The maneuver types 'Bifurcation' (9401) and 'Priority Maneuver' (2104) are ignored
        • Maneuver restriction sequences that contain links that are not incident to the given junction are ignored
        • Maneuver restrictions will be modelled in the natwork topology by expanding nodes with node expanding procedure.

        Specified by:
        run in interface NetworkRunnable
        Parameters:
        network - MATSim network created by NetworkReaderTeleatlas.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - with another Exception in it in the case something goes wrong
